est patch that this skill scaled better and to me it doesn't do that at all once you get 36 AA points to take everything up to SCFM 3 !! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ufastasia.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Fastasia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><table width=111><tr><td style=filter:glow(color=#6633FF strength=1);font-family:arial;font-weight;bold;font-size:'1pt' nowrap><font size=1 color=#FFFFFF face=Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif>Saintly Sorceress</font></td></tr></table></span><br>  Posts: 665<br> <font color=#ffffff>(1/22/02 3:08 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Crit Blasts</span><hr size=1> It scales better now than pre-patch because mastery did not scale AT ALL until SCFM 3 prepatch and then it was only +2 %. So previous to the patch, there was a randomized chance of a spell doing 200-240% plus an additional 2% chance of critting at SCFM 3. It went from 2,4,7, and 7,7,9 to the post patch 2,4,7 and 9,11,13 but no additinal randomized damage. Thus they are saying that it scales better now.<br>
<br>
As a side note that someone else here presented and it appears to be true for every class, there are diminishing returns for Class skills vs Arch skills. That means you will always get more &quot;bang for the buck&quot; regarding power increases with arch than class skills.<br>
<br>
That being said, SCF 3 is a 7% overall power upgrade for 12 points, Spell casting mastery (see other thread) is a 10% overall upgrade for 12 points, and SCFM is a 6% overall power upgrade for 18 points. <br>
<br>
So dimished returns but when added after SCF and SCM it is significant. That is a 23% overall power upgrade combined. That means think of it as having 23% more mana and medding 23% faster (since these skills add the extra without charging more mana). That is significant. Even at level 60.<br>
<br>
just some thoughts,<br>
<br>
